      • findEdge

        public int findEdge(Cities source,
                    Cities destination,
                    GameColor routeColor)
        Returns the edge/route specified with a source, destination, and a color. TIn this method, 3 keys are used to find a unique edge. An example of this would be there are no "shortcuts" nor "alternate paths" between the same source and destination.
        Parameters:
        source - Cities enum specifiying first node.
        destination - Cities enum specifiying last node.
        routeColor - GameColor enum specifying route's color.
        Returns:
        INDEX IF FOUND.
        -1 IF NOT FOUND. Other negative integers specify a specific code.
        -2 if no such source exists.
        -3 if no adjacency list exists.

      • findEdge

        public int findEdge(Cities source,
                    Cities destination,
                    GameColor routeColor,
                    int weight)
        Returns the edge/route specified with a source, destination, and a color. In this method, 4 keys are used to find a unique edge. An example of this would be there are "shortcuts" or an "alternate path" between the same source and destination.
        Parameters:
        source - Cities enum specifiying first node.
        destination - Cities enum specifiying last node.
        routeColor - GameColor enum specifying route's color.
        weight - Weight int specifying route's weight.
        Returns:
        INDEX IF FOUND.
        -1 IF NOT FOUND. Other negative integers specify a specific code.
        -2 if no such source exists.
        -3 if no adjacency list exists.
